    dc:creator "Zhou, Rong; Pan, Zhixiang; Ma, Yitong" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Three new species Willowsia (Collembola: Entomobryidae) from China and notes on W. japonica" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098815>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098820>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098826> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098815>
    dc:description "FIGURES 73−74. Willowsia japonica (Folsom, 1897). 73, habitus; 74, scales. Scale bars: 73 = 500μm; 74 = 10μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5098815/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098820>
    dc:description "FIGURES 75−85. Willowsia japonica (Folsom, 1897). 75, scale; 76, apex of Ant. IV; 77, distal part of Ant. III; 78, distal part of Ant. II; 79, dorsal chaetotaxy of head; 80, lateral process of labial palp; 81, maxillary outer lobe; 82, labium; 83, chaetotaxy of Th. II−III; 84, trochanteral organ; 85, foot complex. Scale bars: 75 = 2μm; 76−78, 80−82, 84 & 85 = 20μm; 79 & 83 = 100μm. Material examined. Two adult female on slides, China, Shaanxi Province, Zhouzhi County, Mazhao Town, 108 National Road, 1386 km, 34°03′35″ N, 108°11′47″ E, 15, July, 2012, collection number: 1115, by Yitong Ma with entomological aspirator. All deposited in NTU." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5098820/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5098826>
    dc:description "FIGURES 86−90. Willowsia japonica (Folsom, 1897). 86, chaetotaxy of Abd. I−III; 87, chaetotaxy of Abd. IV; 88, manubrial plaque; 89, ventro-apical part of manubrium; 90, distal part of dens and mucro. Scale bars: 86 & 87 = 100μm; 88−90 = 20μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5098826/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

